WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.820
To lower the loss, take a small

00:00:02.820 --> 00:00:05.640
step in the direction of the slope.

00:00:05.640 --> 00:00:08.460
Then check the loss, and step again.

00:00:08.460 --> 00:00:10.877
This repeating motion is gradient descent.

00:00:10.877 --> 00:00:13.697
So, gradient descent is repeated small steps

00:00:13.697 --> 00:00:14.100
downhill.
